{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883626160,"sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9a255001LzMnNgrlJFyWub","messageID":"msg_d7ae96d1d001aww9K22tvyZQH4","sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-f1ac4e2c28a6412897884f02815afb36","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: [TO BE FILLED: Overview of MetadataService and data models]\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: [TO BE FILLED]\n18: \n19: [TO BE FILLED: Describe scenarios]\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## Constants Summary\n24: \n25: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n26: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n27: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n28: \n29: ---\n30: \n31: ## Dependencies Summary\n32: \n33: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n34: |---------|---------|---------|\n35: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## File Changes Summary\n40: \n41: | File | Action | Description |\n42: |------|--------|-------------|\n43: | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] | [TO BE FILLED] |\n44: \n45: ---\n46: \n47: ## References\n48: \n49: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n50: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n51: \n52: ---\n53: \n54: ## Validation Checklist\n55: \n56: - [ ] [TO BE FILLED]\n\n(End of file - total 56 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Overview of MetadataService and data models]\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: [TO BE FILLED]\n\n[TO BE FILLED: Describe scenarios]\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883626145,"end":1775883626158}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883626163,"sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9a68d001dRuGNnjd18DkQv","messageID":"msg_d7ae96d1d001aww9K22tvyZQH4","sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-73cb7990441e4ccbbb014c6be25c19da","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n2: \n3: **Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n4: **Language:** Python  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: The `build` command builds a container image from a packaged agent workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version. The command orchestrates: validating prerequisites, incrementing version metadata, building via Docker SDK, and updating metadata with build results.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: `build` command options and defaults\n18: \n19: The system SHALL provide a Typer `build` command with configurable options for workspace, proxy, cloud provider, output, and verbose logging.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Options and defaults\n22: - **GIVEN** the user runs `build`\n23: - **WHEN** options are omitted\n24: - **THEN** defaults SHALL be:\n25:   - `workspace` = `\".\"` (`-f` / `--workspace`, `str`, `show_default=True`)\n26:   - `proxy` = `None` (`-p` / `--proxy`, `Optional[str]`)\n27:   - `cloud_provider` = `None` (`--cloud-provider`, `Optional[str]`)\n28:   - `output` = `None` (`--output`, `Optional[str]`)\n29:   - `verbose` = `False` (`--verbose`, `bool`)\n30: \n31: #### Scenario: Workspace path resolution\n32: - **GIVEN** `workspace` option is provided\n33: - **WHEN** the command executes\n34: - **THEN** `workspace_path` SHALL be resolved as `Path(workspace).resolve()`\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Verbose logging enable\n37: - **GIVEN** `verbose` is `True`\n38: - **WHEN** the command runs\n39: - **THEN** `logging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)` SHALL be called\n40: \n41: ---\n42: \n43: ### Requirement: BuildRuntime class initialization\n44: \n45: The system SHALL construct `BuildRuntime` with verbose flag and orchestrate build workflow.\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: BuildRuntime constructor\n48: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime` is instantiated\n49: - **WHEN** `verbose` parameter is passed\n50: - **THEN** the instance SHALL store `verbose: bool = False` as default and initialize a logger\n51: \n52: #### Scenario: Build method entry point\n53: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build(workspace_path, **options)` is called\n54: - **WHEN** the method executes\n55: - **THEN** it SHALL orchestrate: load metadata → validate prerequisites → increment version → build → update metadata → return result dict\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ### Requirement: Build prerequisites validation\n60: \n61: The system SHALL validate Docker availability and Dockerfile existence before build.\n62: \n63: #### Scenario: Local Docker build prerequisites\n64: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` resolves to `local`\n65: - **WHEN** Docker is unavailable\n66: - **THEN** `BuildRuntime` SHALL raise `RuntimeError(\"Docker is not available or not running\")`\n67: \n68: #### Scenario: Dockerfile existence check\n69: - **GIVEN** `_validate_build_prerequisites(workspace_path)` runs\n70: - **WHEN** `Dockerfile` does not exist at `{workspace_path}/Dockerfile`\n71: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` with message indicating Dockerfile is required\n72: \n73: #### Scenario: Metadata load for build\n74: - **GIVEN** `_validate_build_prerequisites` succeeds\n75: - **WHEN** metadata is loaded\n76: - **THEN** `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` SHALL be called and return `AgentMetadata`\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ### Requirement: Version increment on build\n81: \n82: The system SHALL increment `metadata.version` (patch bump for `X.Y.Z`) before build and revert on failure.\n83: \n84: #### Scenario: Semver patch bump\n85: - **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"1.2.3\"` or `\"v1.2.3\"`\n86: - **WHEN** `_increment_version(workspace_path, metadata)` runs\n87: - **THEN** the version SHALL become `\"1.2.4\"` (patch increment), stripping `v` prefix if present\n88: \n89: #### Scenario: Non-semver version handling\n90: - **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `\"v1.0\"` or `\"1.0\"` (missing patch)\n91: - **WHEN** `_increment_version` runs\n92: - **THEN** the version SHALL append `.1` → `\"v1.0.1\"` or `\"1.0.1\"`\n93: \n94: #### Scenario: Empty version fallback\n95: - **GIVEN** `metadata.version` is `None` or empty\n96: - **WHEN** `_increment_version` runs\n97: - **THEN** the system SHALL generate a timestamp-based version or use `\"{version}-1\"` pattern as fallback\n98: \n99: #### Scenario: Version rollback on build failure\n100: - **GIVEN** a successful version increment occurred\n101: - **WHEN** build fails after increment\n102: - **THEN** the system SHALL revert metadata.version to original value before exiting with error\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: ### Requirement: Local Docker build execution\n107: \n108: The system SHALL use Docker SDK to build images with proxy support via build args.\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: Docker build invocation\n111: - **GIVEN** `_build_local(workspace_path, metadata, options)` is called\n112: - **WHEN** Docker is available\n113: - **THEN** `DockerService.build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag, build_args)` SHALL be invoked\n114: \n115: #### Scenario: Image name and tag\n116: - **GIVEN** metadata contains `agent_name` and incremented `version`\n117: - **WHEN** building locally\n118: - **THEN** `image_name` SHALL be `{agent_name}` and `tag` SHALL be `{version}` or `\"latest\"` as default\n119: \n120: #### Scenario: Proxy build args\n121: - **GIVEN** `--proxy` option is provided with URL `\"http://proxy.example.com:8080\"`\n122: - **WHEN** `_build_local` constructs `build_args`\n123: - **THEN** `build_args` SHALL include `HTTP_PROXY` and `HTTPS_PROXY` keys with the proxy URL\n124: \n125: #### Scenario: Build result extraction\n126: - **GIVEN** Docker build succeeds\n127: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image` returns\n128: - **THEN** the result SHALL contain: `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ### Requirement: Build metadata update\n133: \n134: The system SHALL persist build results to `agent_metadata.yaml`.\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Update build metadata\n137: - **GIVEN** `_update_build_metadata(workspace_path, metadata, build_result, tag)` is called\n138: - **WHEN** metadata is updated\n139: - **THEN** `metadata.image` SHALL be set as dict with keys:\n140:   - `image_name: str`\n141:   - `image_id: str`\n142:   - `image_size: str`\n143:   - `build_time: str`\n144:   - `tag: str` (default `\"latest\"`)\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Metadata file write\n147: - **GIVEN** metadata is updated with image info\n148: - **WHEN** `MetadataService.save_metadata` runs\n149: - **THEN** the file SHALL be written to `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` using `yaml.dump` with `default_flow_style=False`, `indent=2`, `sort_keys=False`, excluding `None` fields via `model_dump(exclude_none=True)`\n150: \n151: ---\n152: \n153: ### Requirement: DockerService class\n154: \n155: The system SHALL provide `DockerService` for Docker SDK integration with build, push, and remove operations.\n156: \n157: #### Scenario: DockerService constructor\n158: - **GIVEN** `DockerService(verbose: bool = False)` is instantiated\n159: - **WHEN** the constructor runs\n160: - **THEN** `verbose` SHALL be stored and a Docker client SHALL be lazily initialized\n161: \n162: #### Scenario: Check Docker available\n163: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.check_docker_available()` is called\n164: - **WHEN** Docker daemon is running\n165: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`\n166: - **WHEN** Docker daemon is not running or unavailable\n167: - **THEN** it SHALL return `False`\n168: \n169: #### Scenario: Build image\n170: - **GIVEN** Docker is running\n171: - **WHEN** `DockerService.build_image(dockerfile_path, context_path, image_name, tag=\"latest\", build_args=None)` is called\n172: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n173:   - Use `docker.from_env().api.build()` with path=context_path, dockerfile=dockerfile_path, tag=`{image_name}:{tag}`\n174:   - Pass `buildargs` from proxy settings\n175:   - Stream build logs\n176:   - Return dict with `image_name`, `image_id`, `image_size`, `build_time`\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Get image info\n179: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.get_image_info(image_name)` is called\n180: - **WHEN** image exists locally\n181: - **THEN** it SHALL return dict with `image_id`, `image_size` (formatted as human-readable string)\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Push image\n184: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.push_image(image_name, registry_url=None, username=None, password=None)` is called\n185: - **WHEN** credentials are provided\n186: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n187:   - Call `_docker_login_sdk(registry, username, password)` if username and password are non-empty\n188:   - Retag image if `registry_url` differs from image name registry\n189:   - Stream push logs\n190:   - Return dict with `pushed_image`, `push_time`\n191: \n192: #### Scenario: Remove image\n193: - **GIVEN** `DockerService.remove_image(image_name)` is called\n194: - **WHEN** removal succeeds\n195: - **THEN** it SHALL return `True`\n196: - **WHEN** removal fails\n197: - **THEN** it SHALL log a warning and return `False`\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ### Requirement: Cloud build placeholder\n202: \n203: The system SHALL provide a placeholder for cloud build mode with `cloud_provider` option.\n204: \n205: #### Scenario: Cloud build not implemented\n206: - **GIVEN** `build_mode` is `\"cloud\"` or `--cloud-provider` is specified\n207: - **WHEN** `_build_cloud` is called\n208: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `NotImplementedError` with message indicating cloud build is not yet implemented\n209: \n210: ---\n211: \n212: ### Requirement: CLI output and progress display\n213: \n214: The system SHALL display build progress using Rich library.\n215: \n216: #### Scenario: Progress spinner during build\n217: - **GIVEN** `build` command runs\n218: - **WHEN** Docker build is executing\n219: - **THEN** a Rich `Progress` spinner SHALL be displayed with status message\n220: \n221: #### Scenario: Success output\n222: - **GIVEN** build completes without exception\n223: - **WHEN** the command finishes\n224: - **THEN** the CLI SHALL print success message with:\n225:   - `image_name`\n226:   - `image_id`\n227:   - `build_time`\n228:   - `metadata_path` (reported as `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml`)\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Build failure handling\n231: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises an exception\n232: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `True`\n233: - **THEN** `_handle_error(e, \"build\", verbose)` SHALL:\n234:   - Print `Error building agent: {e}` in red\n235:   - Print full traceback\n236:   - Exit with code `1`\n237: \n238: #### Scenario: Build failure without verbose\n239: - **GIVEN** `BuildRuntime.build` raises\n240: - **WHEN** `verbose` is `False`\n241: - **THEN** `_handle_error` SHALL print `Error building agent: {e}` in red and exit with code `1` (no traceback)\n242: \n243: ---\n244: \n245: ### Requirement: Error handling patterns\n246: \n247: The system SHALL use `_handle_error(e, command_name, verbose)` for subcommand exceptions.\n248: \n249: #### Scenario: Handle error function\n250: - **GIVEN** `_handle_error(e: Exception, command_name: str, verbose: bool)` is called\n251: - **WHEN** an exception occurs in `build` command\n252: - **THEN** it SHALL:\n253:   - Print `Error {command_name}: {e}` in red using Rich\n254:   - If `verbose` is `True`, print full traceback via `traceback.print_exc()`\n255:   - Raise `typer.Exit(1)`\n256: \n257: #### Scenario: Subcommand verbose vs global verbose\n258: - **GIVEN** a subcommand's local `--verbose` is `True` but global `-v` was not passed\n259: - **WHEN** an error occurs in that subcommand\n260: - **THEN** traceback SHALL still be printed because `_handle_error` receives the subcommand's `verbose` flag\n261: \n262: ---\n263: \n264: ### Requirement: AgentMetadata image field\n265: \n266: The system SHALL extend `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with `image` field for build results.\n267: \n268: #### Scenario: Image field definition\n269: - **GIVEN** `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model in `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py`\n270: - **WHEN** the model is defined\n271: - **THEN** `image` SHALL be `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` with default `None`\n272: \n273: #### Scenario: Image field structure\n274: - **GIVEN** `metadata.image` is populated after build\n275: - **WHEN** examining the dict\n276: - **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n277:   - `image_name: str`\n278:   - `image_id: str`\n279:   - `image_size: str`\n280:   - `build_time: str`\n281:   - `tag: str`\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ### Requirement: Build command integration with pack\n286: \n287: The system SHALL assume `pack` command has been run to generate Dockerfile.\n288: \n289: #### Scenario: Pack prerequisite assumption\n290: - **GIVEN** `build` command is invoked\n291: - **WHEN** Dockerfile is missing\n292: - **THEN** the system SHALL raise `ValueError` suggesting to run `pack` command first\n293: \n294: #### Scenario: Dockerfile location\n295: - **GIVEN** `pack` generated a Dockerfile\n296: - **WHEN** `build` runs\n297: - **THEN** Dockerfile SHALL be expected at `{workspace}/Dockerfile`\n298: \n299: ---\n300: \n301: ### Requirement: Output option handling\n302: \n303: The system SHALL support `--output` option for build artifacts destination.\n304: \n305: #### Scenario: Output path default\n306: - **GIVEN** `--output` is not specified\n307: - **WHEN** build completes\n308: - **THEN** artifacts remain in the workspace (metadata updated in-place)\n309: \n310: #### Scenario: Output path specified\n311: - **GIVEN** `--output` is specified as a path\n312: - **WHEN** build completes\n313: - **THEN** the system SHALL copy or move artifacts to the specified output path (implementation detail per design)\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ## Constants Summary\n318: \n319: | Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n320: |----------|-------|------|---------|\n321: | `DEFAULT_TAG` | `\"latest\"` | `build_runtime.py` | Default image tag when version is None |\n322: | `DEFAULT_TIMEOUT` | `120` | `docker_service.py` | Default timeout for Docker operations |\n323: \n324: ---\n325: \n326: ## Dependencies Summary\n327: \n328: | Package | Version | Purpose |\n329: |---------|---------|---------|\n330: | `docker` | `>=6.0.0` | Docker SDK for Python; required for local build |\n331: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | Metadata model validation |\n332: | `rich` | `>=13.0.0` | Progress spinner and status output |\n333: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | Metadata file read/write |\n334: | `semver` | `>=3.0.0` | Version bump logic |\n335: | `typer[all]` | `>=0.9.0` | CLI framework |\n336: \n337: ---\n338: \n339: ## File Changes Summary\n340: \n341: | File | Action | Description |\n342: |------|--------|-------------|\n343: | `agentcube/runtime/build_runtime.py` | Added | `BuildRuntime` class with build orchestration |\n344: | `agentcube/services/docker_service.py` | Added | `DockerService` for Docker SDK integration |\n345: | `agentcube/cli/main.py` | Modified | Add `build` Typer command |\n346: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | Modified | Add `image` field to `AgentMetadata` |\n347: | `agentcube/runtime/__init__.py` | Modified | Export `BuildRuntime` |\n348: \n349: ---\n350: \n351: ## References\n352: \n353: - AR-020 — CLI pack command (prerequisite for Dockerfile)\n354: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (consumes built image)\n355: - cli-toolkit/design.md — CLI toolkit architecture\n356: - cli-toolkit/spec.md — CLI specification\n357: - Docker SDK Python: https://docker-py.readthedocs.io/\n358: \n359: ---\n360: \n361: ## Validation Checklist\n362: \n363: - [ ] `build` command with default options builds image successfully\n364: - [ ] `--verbose` flag enables DEBUG logging and traceback on error\n365: - [ ] Docker unavailable raises `RuntimeError` with appropriate message\n366: - [ ] Missing Dockerfile raises `ValueError` suggesting to run `pack`\n367: - [ ] Version increment follows semver pattern (X.Y.Z → X.Y.Z+1)\n368: - [ ] Version rollback occurs when build fails\n369: - [ ] Proxy option passes build args to Docker\n370: - [ ] Metadata updated with `image` dict after successful build\n371: - [ ] `_handle_error` prints error and exits with code 1\n372: - [ ] Rich Progress spinner displayed during build\n\n(End of file - total 372 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-021 — CLI build 命令\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThe `build` command builds a container image from a packaged agent workspace using local Docker when `build_mode` is `local` (default in metadata), with optional proxy and tag derived from metadata version. The command orchestrates: validating prerequisites, incrementing version metadata, building via Docker SDK, and updating metadata with build results.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: `build` command options and defaults\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Typer `build` command with configurable options for workspace, proxy, cloud provider, output, and verbose logging.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-021/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883626147,"end":1775883626160}}}}
