{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883638532,"sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9d6d40016m8HDilEAYwBUk","messageID":"msg_d7ae9a6ef001tbL96GyKl4lXDL","sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-02d43683227f45a9bcec01cfe9be1cab","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deployment Design\n2: \n3: Source tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n4: \n5: ## Chart.yaml\n6: \n7: | Field | Value |\n8: |--------|--------|\n9: | `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n10: | `name` | `agentcube` |\n11: | `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n12: | `version` | `0.1.0` |\n13: | `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n14: \n15: ## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n16: \n17: | Path | Type | Default |\n18: |------|------|---------|\n19: | `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n20: | `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n21: | `fullnameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |\n22: | `redis.addr` | string | `\"\"` |\n23: | `redis.password` | string | `\"\"` |\n24: | `router.replicas` | int | `1` |\n25: | `router.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` |\n26: | `router.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n27: | `router.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n28: | `router.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n29: | `router.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n30: | `router.service.targetPort` | int | `8080` |\n31: | `router.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n32: | `router.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n33: | `router.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n34: | `router.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n35: | `router.config` | object | `{}` |\n36: | `router.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n37: | `router.serviceAccountName` | string | `\"\"` |\n38: | `router.rbac.create` | bool | `false` |\n39: | `workloadmanager.replicas` | int | `1` |\n40: | `workloadmanager.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` |\n41: | `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n42: | `workloadmanager.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n43: | `workloadmanager.service.type` | string | `ClusterIP` |\n44: | `workloadmanager.service.port` | int | `8080` |\n45: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu` | string | `500m` |\n46: | `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory` | string | `512Mi` |\n47: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu` | string | `100m` |\n48: | `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory` | string | `128Mi` |\n49: | `workloadmanager.extraEnv` | array | `[]` |\n50: | `volcano.scheduler.enabled` | bool | `false` |\n51: | `volcano.scheduler.replicas` | int | `1` |\n52: | `volcano.scheduler.image.repository` | string | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` |\n53: | `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy` | string | `IfNotPresent` |\n54: | `volcano.scheduler.image.tag` | string | `latest` |\n55: \n56: Comments in `values.yaml` state Redis settings “must be provided by the user during installation”; defaults are still empty strings.\n57: \n58: ## Template files (`manifests/charts/base/templates/`)\n59: \n60: ### `workloadmanager.yaml`\n61: \n62: | Kind | Name | Namespace | Notes |\n63: |------|------|-----------|--------|\n64: | `Deployment` | `workloadmanager` | `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` | `replicas`: `workloadmanager.replicas`; `serviceAccountName`: `workloadmanager`; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `workloadmanager`; image `repository:tag`; `imagePullPolicy`; port `http` → `workloadmanager.service.port`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef `metadata.namespace`), `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `REDIS_ADDR`, plus `workloadmanager.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, `--runtime-class-name=` (empty); **resources**: from values; **liveness/readiness**: HTTP GET `/health` on service port, delays 10s/10s and 5s/5s |\n65: | `Service` | `workloadmanager` | release ns | `type`: `workloadmanager.service.type`; port & `targetPort`: `workloadmanager.service.port`; selector `app: workloadmanager` |\n66: \n67: ### `agentcube-router.yaml`\n68: \n69: | Kind | Name | Notes |\n70: |------|------|--------|\n71: | `Deployment` | `agentcube-router` | `replicas`: `router.replicas`; **conditional** `serviceAccountName` if `router.serviceAccountName` non-empty; optional `imagePullSecrets`; container `agentcube-router`; image from `router.image`; container port `router.service.targetPort`; **env**: `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` (fieldRef), `REDIS_ADDR`, `REDIS_PASSWORD`, `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ workloadmanager.service.port }}`, plus `router.extraEnv`; **args**: `--port={{ router.service.targetPort }}`, `--debug`; **resources** from values; **liveness** `/health/live`, **readiness** `/health/ready` on targetPort, 1s initial, 2s period |\n72: | `Service` | `agentcube-router` | `type` `router.service.type`; `port` `router.service.port`, `targetPort` `router.service.targetPort`; selector `app: agentcube-router` |\n73: \n74: ### `rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n75: \n76: | Kind | Name | Scope | Notes |\n77: |------|------|-------|--------|\n78: | `ServiceAccount` | `workloadmanager` | release namespace | — |\n79: | `ClusterRole` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | rules below |\n80: | `ClusterRoleBinding` | `workloadmanager` | cluster | binds `ClusterRole/workloadmanager` to `ServiceAccount/workloadmanager` in release namespace |\n81: \n82: ### `rbac-router.yaml`\n83: \n84: Rendered **only if** `router.rbac.create` is true.\n85: \n86: | Kind | Name pattern | Notes |\n87: |------|--------------|--------|\n88: | `ServiceAccount` | `{{ router.serviceAccountName \\| default \"agentcube-router\" }}` | release namespace |\n89: | `Role` | same as SA name | rules: `secrets` in `\"\"` apiGroup, full verb set `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n90: | `RoleBinding` | same | subject: SA above; `Role` ref same name |\n91: \n92: ### `volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n93: \n94: Rendered **only if** `volcano.scheduler.enabled`.\n95: \n96: Creates (in order in file): `ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler`; `ConfigMap/volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` with key `agent-scheduler.conf` (actions `allocate`, tiers predicates/nodeorder); `ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler` (large rule set — see RBAC section); `ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role`; `Service/volcano-agent-scheduler-service` (port 8080 metrics annotations); `Deployment/volcano-agent-scheduler` with `replicas` from `volcano.scheduler.replicas`, image from values, args including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`, security contexts, volumes for config + emptyDir.\n97: \n98: ## RBAC rules (exact apiGroups / resources / verbs)\n99: \n100: ### ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n101: \n102: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n103: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n104: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n105: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n106: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n107: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n108: | `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n109: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n110: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n111: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n112: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n113: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n114: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n115: | `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n116: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n117: \n118: ### Role `router` (optional)\n119: \n120: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n121: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n122: | `\"\"` | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n123: \n124: ### ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` (when enabled)\n125: \n126: | apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n127: |-----------|-----------|-------|\n128: | `apiextensions.k8s.io` | `customresourcedefinitions` | `create,get,list,watch,delete` |\n129: | `\"\"` | `events` | `create,list,watch,update,patch` |\n130: | `\"\"` | `pods` | `get,list,watch,patch,delete` |\n131: | `\"\"` | `pods/status` | `update` |\n132: | `\"\"` | `pods/binding` | `create` |\n133: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumeclaims` | `list,watch,update` |\n134: | `\"\"` | `persistentvolumes` | `list,watch,update` |\n135: | `\"\"` | `namespaces,services,replicationcontrollers` | `list,watch,get` |\n136: | `\"\"` | `resourcequotas` | `list,watch` |\n137: | `\"\"` | `nodes` | `get,list,watch,update,patch` |\n138: | `storage.k8s.io` | `storageclasses,csinodes,csidrivers,csistoragecapacities,volumeattachments` | `list,watch` |\n139: | `policy` | `poddisruptionbudgets` | `list,watch` |\n140: | `scheduling.k8s.io` | `priorityclasses` | `get,list,watch` |\n141: | `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io`, `scheduling.volcano.sh` | `podgroups` | `list,watch,update` |\n142: | `\"\"` | `configmaps` | `get,list,watch,create,delete,update` |\n143: | `apps` | `daemonsets,replicasets,statefulsets` | `list,watch,get` |\n144: | `coordination.k8s.io` | `leases` | `get,create,update,watch` |\n145: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch` |\n146: | `resource.k8s.io` | `resourceclaims/status` | `update` |\n147: | `resource.k8s.io` | `deviceclasses,resourceslices` | `get,list,watch,create` |\n148: | `shard.volcano.sh` | `nodeshards` | `list,watch,get,update` |\n149: \n150: ## CRD definitions shipped (`manifests/charts/base/crds/`)\n151: \n152: | File | CRD `metadata.name` | group | versions | scope | Notes |\n153: |------|---------------------|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n154: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | `agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` (served+storage); printer column Age | `Namespaced` | `openAPIV3Schema` includes root fields `apiVersion`, `kind`, `metadata`, `spec`, `status`. **spec.required**: `maxSessionDuration`, `podTemplate`, `sessionTimeout`, `targetPort`. **Key spec fields**: `maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`); `sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`); `targetPort` (array of port objects: required `port`, `protocol` enum HTTP/HTTPS, optional `name`, `pathPrefix`); `podTemplate` (annotations, labels, nested `spec` = full PodSpec-shaped schema). **status**: conditions, etc. Annotation `controller-gen.kubebuilder.io/version: v0.17.2` |\n155: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | `codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `v1alpha1` | `Namespaced` | **spec** includes `authMode` enum `picod|none` default `picod`; `maxSessionDuration` default `8h`; `sessionTimeout` default `15m`; `ports` (same TargetPort shape as above); `template` (image, command, args, env, resources, runtimeClassName, etc.); optional `warmPoolSize` int32. **spec.required**: `template`. **status**: `conditions`, `ready`; subresource `status`. Same controller-gen version annotation |\n156: \n157: ## Dockerfiles\n158: \n159: ### `docker/Dockerfile` (workloadmanager)\n160: \n161: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n162: |-------|------|---------|\n163: | builder | `golang:1.24.9-alpine` | `WORKDIR /workspace`; copy `go.mod`/`go.sum`; `go mod download`; copy `cmd/`, `pkg/`; build `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=${TARGETOS} GOARCH=${TARGETARCH} go build -ldflags=\"-s -w\" -o workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` with BuildKit cache mounts |\n164: | runtime | `alpine:3.19` | `apk add ca-certificates`; `WORKDIR /app`; copy binary; `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`; `USER apiserver`; `EXPOSE 8080`; `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`; `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]` |\n165: \n166: Build args: `TARGETOS=linux`, `TARGETARCH` (implicit platform).\n167: \n168: ### `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n169: \n170: Same pattern as workloadmanager builder, plus `COPY client-go/ client-go/`; output binary `agentcube-router` from `./cmd/router`; runtime user `router` UID 1000; `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`.\n171: \n172: ### `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n173: \n174: | Stage | Base | Purpose |\n175: |-------|------|---------|\n176: | builder | `golang:1.24.4` | `WORKDIR /app`; copy mod files; download; `COPY . .`; build `picod` from `./cmd/picod` with `CGO_ENABLED=0` |\n177: | runtime | `ubuntu:24.04` | `apt-get install -y python3`; `WORKDIR /root/`; copy binary; **runs as root** (comment: chattr on pubkey + sandbox permissions); `ENTRYPOINT [\"./picod\"]` |\n178: \n179: ## Makefile — variables (key)\n180: \n181: | Variable | Default / definition |\n182: |----------|----------------------|\n183: | `HUB` | `ghcr.io/volcano-sh` |\n184: | `TAG` | `latest` |\n185: | `PROJECT_DIR` | directory of Makefile |\n186: | `GOBIN` | from `go env` |\n187: | `CONTAINER_TOOL` | `docker` |\n188: | `SHELL` | `/usr/bin/env bash -o pipefail` |\n189: | `LOCALBIN` | `$(shell pwd)/bin` |\n190: | `CONTROLLER_GEN` | `$(LOCALBIN)/controller-gen` |\n191: | `GOLANGCI_LINT` | `$(LOCALBIN)/golangci-lint` |\n192: | `CONTROLLER_TOOLS_VERSION` | `v0.17.2` |\n193: | `GOLANGCI_LINT_VERSION` | `v1.64.1` |\n194: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE` | `workloadmanager:latest` |\n195: | `ROUTER_IMAGE` | `agentcube-router:latest` |\n196: | `PICOD_IMAGE` | `picod:latest` |\n197: | `IMAGE_REGISTRY` | `\"\"` |\n198: | `E2E_CLUSTER_NAME` | `agentcube-e2e` |\n199: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_REPO` | `https://github.com/kubernetes-sigs/agent-sandbox.git` |\n200: | `AGENT_SANDBOX_VERSION` | `main` (Makefile comment; E2E script overrides — see CI design) |\n201: \n202: ## Makefile — targets\n203: \n204: | Target | Depends / notes |\n205: |--------|-----------------|\n206: | `all` | → `build` |\n207: | `help` | awk help from `##` comments |\n208: | `gen-crd` | `controller-gen`; `crd paths=./pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/...` → `manifests/charts/base/crds` |\n209: | `generate` | `controller-gen object` + `gen-crd` + `go mod tidy` |\n210: | `gen-client` | `bash hack/update-codegen.sh`; `go mod tidy` |\n211: | `gen-all` | `generate` + `gen-client` |\n212: | `gen-check` | `gen-all` then `git diff --exit-code` |\n213: | `build` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/workloadmanager ./cmd/workload-manager` |\n214: | `build-agentd` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentd ./cmd/agentd` |\n215: | `build-router` | `generate`; `go build -o bin/agentcube-router ./cmd/router` |\n216: | `build-all` | `build` + `build-agentd` + `build-router` |\n217: | `run` | `go run ./cmd/workload-manager/main.go --port=8080 --ssh-username=sandbox --ssh-port=22` |\n218: | `run-local` | same with `--kubeconfig=${HOME}/.kube/config` |\n219: | `run-router` | `go run ./cmd/router/main.go --port=8080 --debug` |\n220: | `clean` | `rm -rf bin/` and root binaries |\n221: | `deps` | `go mod download`; `go mod tidy` |\n222: | `update-deps` | `go get -u ./...`; `go mod tidy` |\n223: | `test` | `go test -v ./...` |\n224: | `fmt` | `go fmt ./...` |\n225: | `vet` | `go vet ./...` |\n226: | `lint` | `$(GOLANGCI_LINT) run ./...` |\n227: | `gen-copyright` | `hack/update-copyright.sh` |\n228: | `install` | `build` + `sudo cp bin/workloadmanager /usr/local/bin/` |\n229: | `docker-build` | `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE) .` |\n230: | `docker-buildx` | buildx linux/amd64,arm64 |\n231: | `docker-buildx-push` | requires `IMAGE_REGISTRY`; buildx `--push` |\n232: | `docker-push` | tag+push workloadmanager |\n233: | `kind-load` | `kind load docker-image $(WORKLOAD_MANAGER_IMAGE)` |\n234: | `docker-build-router` / `docker-buildx-router` / `docker-buildx-push-router` / `docker-push-router` / `kind-load-router` | same pattern for router image |\n235: | `docker-build-picod` / `docker-buildx-picod` / `docker-buildx-push-picod` / `docker-push-picod` | same for picod |\n236: | `controller-gen` / `golangci-lint` | download via `go-install-tool` macro |\n237: | `e2e` | `./test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` |\n238: | `e2e-clean` | `kind delete cluster --name $(E2E_CLUSTER_NAME)`; `rm -rf /tmp/agent-sandbox` |\n239: | `build-python-sdk` | copy `LICENSE` to `sdk-python`, `python3 -m build` in `sdk-python`, remove copied LICENSE |\n240: \n241: ## hack/ scripts\n242: \n243: | File | Purpose |\n244: |------|---------|\n245: | `hack/update-codegen.sh` | Runs `k8s.io/code-generator` **v0.34.1**: sources `kube_codegen.sh`, calls `kube::codegen::gen_client --with-watch --output-dir client-go --output-pkg github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/client-go --boilerplate hack/boilerplate.go.txt --one-input-api runtime/v1alpha1` on `pkg/apis`; post-processes lister files with `sed` to append `.GroupResource()` for codeinterpreter/agentruntime resources |\n246: | `hack/update-copyright.sh` | Prepends Apache/Volcano boilerplate to `*.go` and `*.py` under git root (excluding vendor/venv) if missing “Copyright The Volcano Authors”; uses `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` / `hack/boilerplate.py.txt`; requires `sponge` (moreutils) |\n247: | `hack/boilerplate.go.txt` | Go file header template |\n248: | `hack/boilerplate.py.txt` | Python file header template |\n249: \n250: ## Helm / E2E reference command (from `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh`)\n251: \n252: Illustrative install used in E2E:\n253: \n254: ```bash\n255: helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n256:   --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n257:   --create-namespace \\\n258:   --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n259:   --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n260:   --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n261:   --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n262:   --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"},{\"name\":\"JWT_KEY_SECRET_NAMESPACE\",\"value\":\"agentcube\"}]' \\\n263:   --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n264:   --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n265:   --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n266:   --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n267:   --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[{\"name\":\"REDIS_PASSWORD_REQUIRED\",\"value\":\"false\"}]' \\\n268:   --wait\n269: ```\n270: \n271: Images are expected to be loaded into Kind with local names `workloadmanager:latest`, `agentcube-router:latest`, `picod:latest` after `make docker-build` variants.\n\n(End of file - total 271 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deployment Design\n\nSource tree: `/tmp/agentcube-ref` (reference clone). Paths below are relative to repository root unless noted.\n\n## Chart.yaml\n\n| Field | Value |\n|--------|--------|\n| `apiVersion` | `v1` |\n| `name` | `agentcube` |\n| `description` | `A Helm chart for AgentCube` |\n| `version` | `0.1.0` |\n| `appVersion` | `1.0.0` |\n\n## values.yaml — full key tree (type & default)\n\n| Path | Type | Default |\n|------|------|---------|\n| `imagePullSecrets` | array | `[]` |\n| `nameOverride` | string | `\"\"` |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/deployment/design.md","time":{"start":1775883638497,"end":1775883638529}}}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1775883638562,"sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9d703001ChNT4hoNR5wOtM","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","messageID":"msg_d7ae9a6ef001tbL96GyKl4lXDL","sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":35671,"input":20415,"output":153,"reasoning":0,"cache":{"write":0,"read":15103}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1775883641070,"sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae9e0ea001dP4MEmCzWpYsBF","messageID":"msg_d7ae9d74e001Xw54A7DtSZGgbX","sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","snapshot":"f33c5114db06c230ebdbad281b75532a26b6f114","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883785829,"sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","part":{"id":"prt_d7aec15fb001TyeJPvKwEGP5wz","messageID":"msg_d7ae9d74e001Xw54A7DtSZGgbX","sessionID":"ses_28516ce0affeNO7jy2MySbQ1bC","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-d04f793dec7f43378d4001cd2f473d4b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-030 — Helm Chart 模板与 Values\n\n**Module:** `manifests`  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** L\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the official Helm Chart for AgentCube deployment, providing parameterized Kubernetes manifests for all core components (workloadmanager, router, agentd, redis) with configurable values for image registry, replicas, resources, and environment-specific overrides.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: Chart.yaml metadata\n\nThe system SHALL provide a Helm Chart metadata file with correct API version and component information.\n\n#### Scenario: Chart.yaml structure\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` is created\n- **WHEN** the file is written\n- **THEN** it SHALL contain:\n  - `apiVersion: v1`\n  - `name: agentcube`\n  - `description: A Helm chart for AgentCube`\n  - `version: 0.1.0` (chart version)\n  - `appVersion: 1.0.0` (application version)\n\n#### Scenario: Chart dependencies\n- **GIVEN** Chart.yaml defines optional subchart dependencies\n- **WHEN** external charts are needed\n- **THEN** dependencies SHALL be listed in `dependencies` array with `name`, `version`, `repository`, and optional `condition` for enabling/disabling\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: values.yaml default configuration\n\nThe system SHALL provide comprehensive default values for all deployable components.\n\n#### Scenario: Global values section\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` is created\n- **WHEN** global configuration is defined\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `imagePullSecrets: []` (array of secret names for private registries)\n  - `nameOverride: \"\"` (partial name override)\n  - `fullnameOverride: \"\"` (full name override)\n\n#### Scenario: Redis connection values\n- **GIVEN** redis configuration is needed for router and workloadmanager\n- **WHEN** values.yaml defines redis settings\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `redis.addr: \"\"` (Redis address, format `host:port`)\n  - `redis.password: \"\"` (Redis password, empty for no auth)\n\n#### Scenario: Router deployment values\n- **GIVEN** router component is configurable\n- **WHEN** values.yaml defines router section\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `router.replicas: 1` (int)\n  - `router.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/agentcube-router` (string)\n  - `router.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (string)\n  - `router.image.tag: latest` (string)\n  - `router.service.type: ClusterIP` (string)\n  - `router.service.port: 8080` (int)\n  - `router.service.targetPort: 8080` (int)\n  - `router.resources.limits.cpu: 500m` (string)\n  - `router.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi` (string)\n  - `router.resources.requests.cpu: 100m` (string)\n  - `router.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi` (string)\n  - `router.config: {}` (object)\n  - `router.extraEnv: []` (array)\n  - `router.serviceAccountName: \"\"` (string)\n  - `router.rbac.create: false` (bool)\n\n#### Scenario: WorkloadManager deployment values\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager component is configurable\n- **WHEN** values.yaml defines workloadmanager section\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `workloadmanager.replicas: 1` (int)\n  - `workloadmanager.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/workloadmanager` (string)\n  - `workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (string)\n  - `workloadmanager.image.tag: latest` (string)\n  - `workloadmanager.service.type: ClusterIP` (string)\n  - `workloadmanager.service.port: 8080` (int)\n  - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.cpu: 500m` (string)\n  - `workloadmanager.resources.limits.memory: 512Mi` (string)\n  - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.cpu: 100m` (string)\n  - `workloadmanager.resources.requests.memory: 128Mi` (string)\n  - `workloadmanager.extraEnv: []` (array)\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano scheduler optional values\n- **GIVEN** volcano scheduler is an optional component\n- **WHEN** values.yaml defines volcano.scheduler section\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `volcano.scheduler.enabled: false` (bool, disabled by default)\n  - `volcano.scheduler.replicas: 1` (int)\n  - `volcano.scheduler.image.repository: ghcr.io/volcano-sh/vc-agent-scheduler` (string)\n  - `volcano.scheduler.image.pullPolicy: IfNotPresent` (string)\n  - `volcano.scheduler.image.tag: latest` (string)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: WorkloadManager Deployment template\n\nThe system SHALL template WorkloadManager Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources, and environment.\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment metadata\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n- **WHEN** helm template executes\n- **THEN** Deployment metadata SHALL include:\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `labels` using helper templates\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment spec replicas\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager Deployment is templated\n- **WHEN** replicas value is specified\n- **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.replicas }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment container image\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager container is defined\n- **WHEN** image values are set\n- **THEN** container image SHALL be:\n  - `image: \"{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.tag }}\"`\n  - `imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.image.pullPolicy }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment environment variables\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager needs namespace and redis config\n- **WHEN** env section is templated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from `fieldRef: metadata.namespace`\n  - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values\n  - `REDIS_ADDR` from values\n  - Extra env from `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.extraEnv }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment container args\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager needs port configuration\n- **WHEN** args are templated\n- **THEN** args SHALL include:\n  - `--port={{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n  - `--runtime-class-name=` (empty string for default)\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment resources\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager has configurable resources\n- **WHEN** resources section is templated\n- **THEN** `resources` SHALL map from `{{ .Values.workloadmanager.resources }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment health probes\n- **GIVEN** workloadmanager needs health endpoints\n- **WHEN** liveness and readiness probes are defined\n- **THEN** both SHALL be HTTP GET:\n  - `path: /health`\n  - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n  - liveness: `initialDelaySeconds: 10`, `periodSeconds: 10`\n  - readiness: `initialDelaySeconds: 5`, `periodSeconds: 5`\n\n#### Scenario: Deployment imagePullSecrets optional\n- **GIVEN** `imagePullSecrets` array in global values\n- **WHEN** array is non-empty\n- **THEN** `spec.template.spec.imagePullSecrets` SHALL be rendered from values\n- **WHEN** array is empty\n- **THEN** `imagePullSecrets` section SHALL be omitted\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: WorkloadManager Service template\n\nThe system SHALL template WorkloadManager Service with configurable type and port.\n\n#### Scenario: Service metadata\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager Service is rendered\n- **WHEN** helm template executes\n- **THEN** Service SHALL have:\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `labels` matching Deployment\n\n#### Scenario: Service spec\n- **GIVEN** Service is templated\n- **WHEN** service values are defined\n- **THEN** Service spec SHALL include:\n  - `type: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.type }}`\n  - `ports` array with:\n    - `port: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n    - `targetPort: {{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n    - `protocol: TCP`\n    - `name: http`\n  - `selector: app: workloadmanager`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Router Deployment template\n\nThe system SHALL template Router Deployment with configurable replicas, image, resources, and environment including Redis and WorkloadManager URLs.\n\n#### Scenario: Router Deployment metadata\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` is rendered\n- **WHEN** helm template executes\n- **THEN** Deployment SHALL have:\n  - `name: agentcube-router`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `labels` using helper templates\n\n#### Scenario: Router Deployment replicas\n- **GIVEN** router Deployment is templated\n- **WHEN** replicas value is specified\n- **THEN** `spec.replicas` SHALL be `{{ .Values.router.replicas }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Router serviceAccountName conditional\n- **GIVEN** router Deployment needs optional service account\n- **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is non-empty\n- **THEN** `spec.template.spec.serviceAccountName` SHALL be set to that value\n- **WHEN** value is empty\n- **THEN** `serviceAccountName` SHALL be omitted (uses default)\n\n#### Scenario: Router container image\n- **GIVEN** router container is defined\n- **WHEN** image values are set\n- **THEN** container image SHALL be:\n  - `image: \"{{ .Values.router.image.repository }}:{{ .Values.router.image.tag }}\"`\n  - `imagePullPolicy: {{ .Values.router.image.pullPolicy }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Router container port\n- **GIVEN** router exposes HTTP port\n- **WHEN** container ports are defined\n- **THEN** `ports` SHALL include:\n  - `containerPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n  - `protocol: TCP`\n  - `name: http`\n\n#### Scenario: Router environment variables\n- **GIVEN** router needs namespace, redis, and workloadmanager config\n- **WHEN** env section is templated\n- **THEN** it SHALL include:\n  - `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` from `fieldRef: metadata.namespace`\n  - `REDIS_ADDR` from values\n  - `REDIS_PASSWORD` from values\n  - `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` = `http://workloadmanager.{{ .Release.Namespace }}.svc.cluster.local:{{ .Values.workloadmanager.service.port }}`\n  - Extra env from `{{ .Values.router.extraEnv }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Router container args\n- **GIVEN** router needs port and debug configuration\n- **WHEN** args are templated\n- **THEN** args SHALL include:\n  - `--port={{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n  - `--debug`\n\n#### Scenario: Router resources\n- **GIVEN** router has configurable resources\n- **WHEN** resources section is templated\n- **THEN** `resources` SHALL map from `{{ .Values.router.resources }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Router health probes\n- **GIVEN** router needs separate liveness and readiness endpoints\n- **WHEN** probes are defined\n- **THEN** probes SHALL be HTTP GET on `{{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`:\n  - liveness: `path: /health/live`, `initialDelaySeconds: 1`, `periodSeconds: 2`\n  - readiness: `path: /health/ready`, `initialDelaySeconds: 1`, `periodSeconds: 2`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Router Service template\n\nThe system SHALL template Router Service with configurable type, port, and targetPort.\n\n#### Scenario: Router Service metadata\n- **GIVEN** Router Service is rendered\n- **WHEN** helm template executes\n- **THEN** Service SHALL have:\n  - `name: agentcube-router`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `labels` matching Deployment\n\n#### Scenario: Router Service spec\n- **GIVEN** Service is templated\n- **WHEN** service values are defined\n- **THEN** Service spec SHALL include:\n  - `type: {{ .Values.router.service.type }}`\n  - `ports` array with:\n    - `port: {{ .Values.router.service.port }}`\n    - `targetPort: {{ .Values.router.service.targetPort }}`\n    - `protocol: TCP`\n    - `name: http`\n  - `selector: app: agentcube-router`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: WorkloadManager RBAC template\n\nThe system SHALL template WorkloadManager RBAC resources (ServiceAccount, ClusterRole, ClusterRoleBinding).\n\n#### Scenario: ServiceAccount for WorkloadManager\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` is rendered\n- **WHEN** helm template executes\n- **THEN** ServiceAccount SHALL have:\n  - `name: workloadmanager`\n  - `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n\n#### Scenario: ClusterRole for WorkloadManager\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager needs cluster-scoped permissions\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole is templated\n- **THEN** ClusterRole `workloadmanager` SHALL have rules:\n\n| apiGroups | resources | verbs |\n|-----------|-----------|-------|\n| `agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxes` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n| `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxclaims` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n| `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxtemplates` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n| `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n| `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io` | `sandboxwarmpools/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/status` | `get,update,patch` |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `codeinterpreters/finalizers` | `update` |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes` | `get,list,watch` |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh` | `agentruntimes/status` | `update,patch` |\n| `\"\"` (core) | `pods` | `get,list,watch` |\n| `authentication.k8s.io` | `tokenreviews` | `create` |\n| `\"\"` (core) | `secrets` | `get,list,watch,create,update,patch,delete` |\n\n#### Scenario: ClusterRoleBinding for WorkloadManager\n- **GIVEN** WorkloadManager ClusterRole needs binding\n- **WHEN** ClusterRoleBinding is templated\n- **THEN** ClusterRoleBinding `workloadmanager` SHALL have:\n  - `subjects`: ServiceAccount `workloadmanager` in `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - `roleRef`: ClusterRole `workloadmanager`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Router RBAC template (conditional)\n\nThe system SHALL conditionally template Router RBAC resources when `router.rbac.create` is true.\n\n#### Scenario: Router RBAC conditional rendering\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.rbac.create }}` is `true`\n- **THEN** ServiceAccount, Role, RoleBinding SHALL be rendered\n- **WHEN** value is `false`\n- **THEN** no RBAC resources SHALL be rendered for router\n\n#### Scenario: Router ServiceAccount name derivation\n- **GIVEN** router RBAC is enabled\n- **WHEN** `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName }}` is non-empty\n- **THEN** ServiceAccount name SHALL be that value\n- **WHEN** value is empty\n- **THEN** ServiceAccount name SHALL default to `agentcube-router`\n\n#### Scenario: Router Role permissions\n- **GIVEN** router needs namespace-scoped secret access\n- **WHEN** Role is templated\n- **THEN** Role SHALL have rules:\n  - `apiGroups: [\"\"]`\n  - `resources: [\"secrets\"]`\n  - `verbs: [\"get\",\"list\",\"watch\",\"create\",\"update\",\"patch\",\"delete\"]`\n\n#### Scenario: Router RoleBinding\n- **GIVEN** router Role needs binding\n- **WHEN** RoleBinding is templated\n- **THEN** RoleBinding SHALL reference:\n  - `subjects`: ServiceAccount with derived name in release namespace\n  - `roleRef`: Role with same name\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Volcano Agent Scheduler template (conditional)\n\nThe system SHALL conditionally template Volcano Agent Scheduler when `volcano.scheduler.enabled` is true.\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano scheduler conditional rendering\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** `{{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}` is `true`\n- **THEN** all scheduler resources SHALL be rendered\n- **WHEN** value is `false`\n- **THEN** no scheduler resources SHALL be rendered\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano scheduler ServiceAccount\n- **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ServiceAccount is templated\n- **THEN** `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano scheduler ConfigMap\n- **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** ConfigMap is templated\n- **THEN** ConfigMap `volcano-agent-scheduler-configmap` SHALL have:\n  - `data.agent-scheduler.conf` containing scheduler configuration with `actions: [\"allocate\"]` and `tiers`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano scheduler ClusterRole\n- **GIVEN** scheduler needs broad cluster permissions\n- **WHEN** ClusterRole is templated\n- **THEN** ClusterRole `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL have rules covering:\n  - `apiextensions.k8s.io/customresourcedefinitions`\n  - `\"\"` (core): `events, pods, pods/status, pods/binding, persistentvolumeclaims, persistentvolumes, namespaces, services, replicationcontrollers, resourcequotas, nodes, configmaps`\n  - `storage.k8s.io`: storage-related resources\n  - `policy/poddisruptionbudgets`\n  - `scheduling.k8s.io/priorityclasses`\n  - `scheduling.volcano.sh/podgroups`\n  - `apps`: daemonsets, replicasets, statefulsets\n  - `coordination.k8s.io/leases`\n  - `resource.k8s.io`: resource claims\n  - `shard.volcano.sh/nodeshards`\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano scheduler Deployment\n- **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** Deployment is templated\n- **THEN** Deployment `volcano-agent-scheduler` SHALL have:\n  - `replicas: {{ .Values.volcano.scheduler.replicas }}`\n  - `image` from volcano.scheduler.image values\n  - `args` including `--scheduler-name=agent-scheduler`\n  - `securityContext` for container\n  - `volumes` for config and emptyDir\n\n#### Scenario: Volcano scheduler Service\n- **GIVEN** scheduler is enabled\n- **WHEN** Service is templated\n- **THEN** Service `volcano-agent-scheduler-service` SHALL have:\n  - `port: 8080`\n  - `annotations` for metrics\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: _helpers.tpl named templates\n\nThe system SHALL provide helper templates for consistent naming and labeling across all resources.\n\n#### Scenario: Name helper template\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` is created\n- **WHEN** `{{ template \"agentcube.name\" . }}` is invoked\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `.Chart.Name` or nameOverride\n\n#### Scenario: Fullname helper template\n- **GIVEN** helpers tpl defines fullname\n- **WHEN** `{{ template \"agentcube.fullname\" . }}` is invoked\n- **THEN** it SHALL return fully qualified resource name using release name + chart name + overrides\n\n#### Scenario: Labels helper template\n- **GIVEN** helpers tpl defines labels\n- **WHEN** `{{ include \"agentcube.labels\" . }}` is invoked\n- **THEN** it SHALL return standard labels:\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/name: {{ template \"agentcube.name\" . }}`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/instance: {{ .Release.Name }}`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/version: {{ .Chart.AppVersion }}`\n  - `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: {{ .Release.Service }}`\n\n#### Scenario: Image helper template\n- **GIVEN** helpers tpl defines image helper\n- **WHEN** image path needs construction\n- **THEN** helper SHALL combine repository and tag with proper format\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: CRD files in crds/ directory\n\nThe system SHALL ship CRD definitions that are installed before templates.\n\n#### Scenario: CRD directory location\n- **GIVEN** CRDs need to be bundled\n- **WHEN** chart is packaged\n- **THEN** CRDs SHALL be in `manifests/charts/base/crds/` directory\n\n#### Scenario: AgentRuntime CRD\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** CRD is installed\n- **THEN** CRD SHALL define:\n  - `metadata.name: agentruntimes.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n  - `group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n  - `versions: v1alpha1` (served + storage)\n  - `scope: Namespaced`\n  - `spec.required: maxSessionDuration, podTemplate, sessionTimeout, targetPort`\n  - `spec.maxSessionDuration` (string, default `8h`)\n  - `spec.sessionTimeout` (string, default `15m`)\n  - `spec.targetPort` (array of port objects)\n  - `spec.podTemplate` (full PodSpec-shaped schema)\n\n#### Scenario: CodeInterpreter CRD\n- **GIVEN** `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` exists\n- **WHEN** CRD is installed\n- **THEN** CRD SHALL define:\n  - `metadata.name: codeinterpreters.runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n  - `group: runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh`\n  - `versions: v1alpha1`\n  - `scope: Namespaced`\n  - `spec.authMode` (enum `picod|none`, default `picod`)\n  - `spec.maxSessionDuration` (default `8h`)\n  - `spec.sessionTimeout` (default `15m`)\n  - `spec.template` (required: image, command, args, env, resources)\n  - `spec.warmPoolSize` (optional int32)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Helm lint and template validation\n\nThe system SHALL pass Helm lint and produce valid rendered templates.\n\n#### Scenario: Helm lint passes\n- **GIVEN** chart is complete\n- **WHEN** `helm lint manifests/charts/base` is executed\n- **THEN** lint SHALL pass with no errors\n\n#### Scenario: Template rendering produces valid YAML\n- **GIVEN** chart templates are complete\n- **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base` is executed\n- **THEN** output SHALL be valid Kubernetes YAML for all enabled components\n\n#### Scenario: Template rendering with values override\n- **GIVEN** custom values are provided\n- **WHEN** `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base -f custom-values.yaml` is executed\n- **THEN** output SHALL reflect custom values correctly\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: E2E deployment integration\n\nThe system SHALL support E2E test deployment via helm upgrade --install.\n\n#### Scenario: E2E Helm install command\n- **GIVEN** E2E test environment (Kind cluster)\n- **WHEN** `test/e2e/run_e2e.sh` deploys AgentCube\n- **THEN** command SHALL be:\n  ```bash\n  helm upgrade --install agentcube manifests/charts/base \\\n    --namespace \"${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}\" \\\n    --create-namespace \\\n    --set redis.addr=\"redis.${AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE}.svc.cluster.local:6379\" \\\n    --set redis.password=\"\" \\\n    --set workloadmanager.image.repository=\"workloadmanager\" \\\n    --set workloadmanager.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n    --set-json 'workloadmanager.extraEnv=[...]' \\\n    --set router.image.repository=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n    --set router.image.tag=\"latest\" \\\n    --set router.rbac.create=true \\\n    --set router.serviceAccountName=\"agentcube-router\" \\\n    --set-json 'router.extraEnv=[...]' \\\n    --wait\n  ```\n\n#### Scenario: E2E local image references\n- **GIVEN** images are built and loaded into Kind\n- **WHEN** helm install runs\n- **THEN** image repository SHALL reference local image names (e.g., `workloadmanager`, `agentcube-router`) without registry prefix\n\n---\n\n## Constants Summary\n\n| Constant | Value | File | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|------|---------|\n| `DEFAULT_PORT` | `8080` | `values.yaml` | Default HTTP port for services |\n| `REDIS_PORT` | `6379` | `values.yaml` | Default Redis port |\n| `DEFAULT_REPLICAS` | `1` | `values.yaml` | Default replica count |\n| `DEFAULT_CPU_LIMIT` | `500m` | `values.yaml` | Default CPU limit |\n| `DEFAULT_MEMORY_LIMIT` | `512Mi` | `values.yaml` | Default memory limit |\n| `DEFAULT_CPU_REQUEST` | `100m` | `values.yaml` | Default CPU request |\n| `DEFAULT_MEMORY_REQUEST` | `128Mi` | `values.yaml` | Default memory request |\n| `DEFAULT_IMAGE_PULL_POLICY` | `IfNotPresent` | `values.yaml` | Default pull policy |\n| `DEFAULT_SESSION_TIMEOUT` | `15m` | CRDs | Default session timeout |\n| `DEFAULT_MAX_SESSION_DURATION` | `8h` | CRDs | Default max session duration |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies Summary\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `Helm 3` | `>=3.8.0` | Template rendering and release management |\n| `Kubernetes` | `>=1.24` | API versions for Deployment, Service, RBAC, CRD resources |\n| `agent-sandbox CRDs` | `main` | Sandbox CRDs from sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox |\n| `controller-gen` | `v0.17.2` | CRD generation from Go types |\n\n---\n\n## File Changes Summary\n\n| File | Action | Description |\n|------|--------|-------------|\n| `manifests/charts/base/Chart.yaml` | Added | Helm Chart metadata |\n| `manifests/charts/base/values.yaml` | Added | Default configuration values |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/_helpers.tpl` | Added | Named template helpers |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/workloadmanager.yaml` | Added | WorkloadManager Deployment + Service |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/agentcube-router.yaml` | Added | Router Deployment + Service |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml` | Added | WorkloadManager RBAC resources |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml` | Added | Router RBAC (conditional) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml` | Added | Volcano scheduler (conditional) |\n| `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_agentruntimes.yaml` | Added | AgentRuntime CRD definition |\n| `manifests/charts/base/crds/runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh_codeinterpreters.yaml` | Added | CodeInterpreter CRD definition |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- proposal.md — AR-030 proposal with scope and implementation checklist\n- deployment/design.md — Reference implementation details\n- ci-cd/design.md — E2E Helm usage patterns\n- sandbox-orchestration/design.md — Component configuration details\n- Helm 3 Documentation — Chart structure, templates, values best practices\n- Kubernetes API Reference — Deployment, Service, RBAC schemas\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] `helm lint manifests/charts/base` passes with no errors\n- [ ] `helm template agentcube manifests/charts/base` produces valid YAML\n- [ ] WorkloadManager Deployment renders with correct image, env, probes\n- [ ] WorkloadManager Service renders with correct port and selector\n- [ ] Router Deployment renders with Redis and WorkloadManager URLs in env\n- [ ] Router Service renders with correct port mapping\n- [ ] WorkloadManager ClusterRole has all required RBAC rules\n- [ ] Router RBAC renders conditionally when `router.rbac.create=true`\n- [ ] Volcano scheduler renders conditionally when `volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n- [ ] `_helpers.tpl` provides name, fullname, labels templates\n- [ ] CRD files are valid and match controller-gen output\n- [ ] E2E script can deploy with `helm upgrade --install`\n- [ ] Custom values override defaults correctly"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-030/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775883785798,"end":1775883785825}}}}
